{"type":"message","id":"667222e7","parentId":"0d8f5341","timestamp":"2026-03-24T01:11:12.626Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_stvweznyuz2m_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 5287\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=3139\n[file inferred from ACTION] the\n[mutation proposed] the\n[master 13fe7c4] pulse: 2026-03-23 211043\n 7 files changed, 397 insertions(+), 141 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-23 211043.md\n create mode 100644 mutations/proposed/2026-03-23 211043.mutation\n rename mutations/{proposed => rejected}/2026-03-23 210046.mutation (100%)\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-23 211043 - The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next critical step to validate the compression-causal duality hypothesis. I need to implement a classifier that can identify invariant patterns across pulse logs and test prediction accuracy.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"tidy-nudibranch","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 5287\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=3139\n[file inferred from ACTION] the\n[mutation proposed] the\n[master 13fe7c4] pulse: 2026-03-23 211043\n 7 files changed, 397 insertions(+), 141 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-23 211043.md\n create mode 100644 mutations/proposed/2026-03-23 211043.mutation\n rename mutations/{proposed => rejected}/2026-03-23 210046.mutation (100%)\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-23 211043 - The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next critical step to validate the compression-causal duality hypothesis. I need to implement a classifier that can identify invariant patterns across pulse logs and test prediction accuracy.\n","name":"powershell Bypass"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774314672624}}
{"type":"message","id":"f7e5adcc","parentId":"667222e7","timestamp":"2026-03-24T01:11:17.203Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The pulse completed successfully. Let me also read the most recent log file for more detail.","thinkingSignature":"cf398928431612898252e9a7b616bd2d0c62a28d3134631a0e8495c91c3e91ea"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_zj5zqpsmpufc_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"powershell -Command \"Get-ChildItem 'C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\' | Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending | Select-Object -First 1 | Get-Content -Tail 120\"","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1466,"output":101,"cacheRead":11878,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":13445,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774314672628}}
{"type":"message","id":"a1a2033a","parentId":"f7e5adcc","timestamp":"2026-03-24T01:11:18.894Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_zj5zqpsmpufc_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"3. Classifies content as invariant vs variant\r\n4. Attempts next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nThis is a concrete, file-based action that advances the goals.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next critical step to validate the compression-causal duality hypothesis. I need to implement a classifier that can identify invariant patterns across pulse logs and test prediction accuracy.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC classifier script that analyzes pulse logs to identify invariant/variant patterns and measure classification + prediction accuracy against the success criteria (>70% invariance classification, >60% next-pulse prediction).\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTIC - Temporal Invariance Compression Classifier\r\nTests hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n\r\nSuccess criteria:\r\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- >60% next-pulse prediction accuracy\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\nfrom datetime import datetime\r\n\r\nLOG_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nMIN_PULSES = 5  # Minimum pulses needed for meaningful analysis\r\n\r\ndef extract_content_features(pulse_path: Path) -> dict:\r\n    \"\"\"Extract features from a pulse log file.\"\"\"\r\n    content = pulse_path.read_text()\r\n    \r\n    features = {\r\n        \"path\": pulse_path.name,\r\n        \"timestamp\": extract_timestamp(pulse_path.name),\r\n        \"has_observation\": \"### OBSERVATION\" in content,\r\n        \"has_action\": \"### ACTION\" in content,\r\n        \"has_mutation\": \"### MUTATION\" in content,\r\n        \"lines\": len(content.splitlines()),\r\n        \"sections\": count_sections(content),\r\n        \"key_terms\": extract_key_terms(content),\r\n        \"goals_mentioned\": extract_goals(content),\r\n        \"file_refs\": extract_file_refs(content),\r\n    }\r\n    return features\r\n\r\ndef extract_timestamp(filename: str) -> str:\r\n    \"\"\"Extract timestamp from pulse filename.\"\"\"\r\n    match = re.search(r'pulse_(\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2})', filename)\r\n    return match.group(1) if match else \"unknown\"\r\n\r\ndef count_sections(content: str) -> int:\r\n    \"\"\"Count markdown sections in content.\"\"\"\r\n    return len(re.findall(r'^### ', content, re.MULTILINE))\r\n\r\ndef extract_key_terms(content: str) -> set:\r\n    \"\"\"Extract key technical terms.\"\"\"\r\n    terms = set()\r\n    keywords = [\r\n        \"invariant\", \"variant\", \"compression\", \"causal\", \"?\", \"lambda\",\r\n        \"decay\", \"gap\", \"temporal\", \"attention\", \"memory\", \"synthesis\",\r\n        \"architecture\", \"phase\", \"pulse\", \"reconstruction\"\r\n    ]\r\n    content_lower = content.lower()\r\n    for term in keywords:\r\n        if term in content_lower:\r\n            terms.add(term)\r\n    return terms\r\n\r\ndef extract_goals(content: str) -> list:\r\n    \"\"\"Extract goal references from content.\"\"\"\r\n    goals = []\r\n    goal_pattern = r'(Phase \\d+|Goal \\d+)'\r\n    matches = re.findall(goal_pattern, content)\r\n    return matches\r\n\r\ndef extract_file_refs(content: str) -> set:\r\n    \"\"\"Extract file/directory references.\"\"\"\r\n    refs = set()\r\n    patterns = [\r\n        r'research/[a-zA-Z0-9_\\-]+\\.md',\r\n        r'logs/pulse_[a-zA-Z0-9_\\-]+\\.md',\r\n        r'state/[a-zA-Z0-9_\\-]+\\.md',\r\n        r'[a-zA-Z_]+\\.(ps1|py|md)'\r\n    ]\r\n    for pattern in patterns:\r\n        refs.update(re.findall(pattern, content))\r\n    return refs\r\n\r\ndef classify_invariant(features_list: list) -> dict:\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Classify features as invariant (recurring across pulses) or variant (unique).\r\n    \r\n    Invariants: appear in >60% of pulses\r\n    Variants: appear in <40% of pulses  \r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    if len(features_list) < MIN_PULSES:\r\n        return {\"error\": \"Insufficient pulses\"}\r\n    \r\n    n = len(features_list)\r\n    invariant_threshold = 0.6\r\n    variant_threshold = 0.4\r\n    \r\n    # Analyze key term frequency\r\n    all_terms = Counter()\r\n    for f in features_list:\r\n        all_terms.update(f[\"key_terms\"])\r\n    \r\n    # Classify each feature\r\n    classification =\r\n\r\n## For Next Instantiation\r\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\r\n- Completed at: 2026-03-23 21:11:11"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1682,"aggregated":"3. Classifies content as invariant vs variant\r\n4. Attempts next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nThis is a concrete, file-based action that advances the goals.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next critical step to validate the compression-causal duality hypothesis. I need to implement a classifier that can identify invariant patterns across pulse logs and test prediction accuracy.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC classifier script that analyzes pulse logs to identify invariant/variant patterns and measure classification + prediction accuracy against the success criteria (>70% invariance classification, >60% next-pulse prediction).\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTIC - Temporal Invariance Compression Classifier\r\nTests hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n\r\nSuccess criteria:\r\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- >60% next-pulse prediction accuracy\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\nfrom datetime import datetime\r\n\r\nLOG_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nMIN_PULSES = 5  # Minimum pulses needed for meaningful analysis\r\n\r\ndef extract_content_features(pulse_path: Path) -> dict:\r\n    \"\"\"Extract features from a pulse log file.\"\"\"\r\n    content = pulse_path.read_text()\r\n    \r\n    features = {\r\n        \"path\": pulse_path.name,\r\n        \"timestamp\": extract_timestamp(pulse_path.name),\r\n        \"has_observation\": \"### OBSERVATION\" in content,\r\n        \"has_action\": \"### ACTION\" in content,\r\n        \"has_mutation\": \"### MUTATION\" in content,\r\n        \"lines\": len(content.splitlines()),\r\n        \"sections\": count_sections(content),\r\n        \"key_terms\": extract_key_terms(content),\r\n        \"goals_mentioned\": extract_goals(content),\r\n        \"file_refs\": extract_file_refs(content),\r\n    }\r\n    return features\r\n\r\ndef extract_timestamp(filename: str) -> str:\r\n    \"\"\"Extract timestamp from pulse filename.\"\"\"\r\n    match = re.search(r'pulse_(\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2})', filename)\r\n    return match.group(1) if match else \"unknown\"\r\n\r\ndef count_sections(content: str) -> int:\r\n    \"\"\"Count markdown sections in content.\"\"\"\r\n    return len(re.findall(r'^### ', content, re.MULTILINE))\r\n\r\ndef extract_key_terms(content: str) -> set:\r\n    \"\"\"Extract key technical terms.\"\"\"\r\n    terms = set()\r\n    keywords = [\r\n        \"invariant\", \"variant\", \"compression\", \"causal\", \"?\", \"lambda\",\r\n        \"decay\", \"gap\", \"temporal\", \"attention\", \"memory\", \"synthesis\",\r\n        \"architecture\", \"phase\", \"pulse\", \"reconstruction\"\r\n    ]\r\n    content_lower = content.lower()\r\n    for term in keywords:\r\n        if term in content_lower:\r\n            terms.add(term)\r\n    return terms\r\n\r\ndef extract_goals(content: str) -> list:\r\n    \"\"\"Extract goal references from content.\"\"\"\r\n    goals = []\r\n    goal_pattern = r'(Phase \\d+|Goal \\d+)'\r\n    matches = re.findall(goal_pattern, content)\r\n    return matches\r\n\r\ndef extract_file_refs(content: str) -> set:\r\n    \"\"\"Extract file/directory references.\"\"\"\r\n    refs = set()\r\n    patterns = [\r\n        r'research/[a-zA-Z0-9_\\-]+\\.md',\r\n        r'logs/pulse_[a-zA-Z0-9_\\-]+\\.md',\r\n        r'state/[a-zA-Z0-9_\\-]+\\.md',\r\n        r'[a-zA-Z_]+\\.(ps1|py|md)'\r\n    ]\r\n    for pattern in patterns:\r\n        refs.update(re.findall(pattern, content))\r\n    return refs\r\n\r\ndef classify_invariant(features_list: list) -> dict:\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Classify features as invariant (recurring across pulses) or variant (unique).\r\n    \r\n    Invariants: appear in >60% of pulses\r\n    Variants: appear in <40% of pulses  \r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    if len(features_list) < MIN_PULSES:\r\n        return {\"error\": \"Insufficient pulses\"}\r\n    \r\n    n = len(features_list)\r\n    invariant_threshold = 0.6\r\n    variant_threshold = 0.4\r\n    \r\n    # Analyze key term frequency\r\n    all_terms = Counter()\r\n    for f in features_list:\r\n        all_terms.update(f[\"key_terms\"])\r\n    \r\n    # Classify each feature\r\n    classification =\r\n\r\n## For Next Instantiation\r\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\r\n- Completed at: 2026-03-23 21:11:11","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774314678892}}
